  function_response=FunctionResponse(
    id='adk-97c09b20-e65f-4582-80bd-44c2d6bd2c74',
    name='search',
    response={
      'result': """CVE-2006-2369 is an authentication bypass vulnerability primarily affecting RealVNC 4.1.1 and other products that integrate RealVNC, such as AdderLink IP and Cisco CallManager.

This vulnerability allows remote attackers to bypass the authentication process. It occurs because the client can specify an insecure security type, like "Type 1 - None", which the server will accept even if it was not among the security types offered by the server. This flaw was initially demonstrated using a long password.

Successful exploitation of CVE-2006-2369 can lead to unauthenticated, remote access to the VNC server, granting the attacker full control over the session. The vulnerability was published on May 15, 2006 and has been assigned a CVSS 2.0 Base Score of 7.5 (High severity) and a CVSS 3.0 Base Score of 9.8 (Critical severity)."""
    }
  )
)] role='user'
